Hey all!

I'd love to make a menu option in nteract to denote a parameter cell in a single click within the nteract web app. As for design, for the moment just to make this simple with our current setup, I'd just be adding it to our menu:

<img width="173" alt="screen shot 2018-01-25 at 8 22 05 am" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/836375/35399337-dd354870-01a8-11e8-9415-c1470228c7ff.png">

When it _is_ a parameterized cell, we can show a special border on the top or otherwise to indicate that it's a parameter cell. Haven't thought much on the design much here other than that we want some way to see it visually as users.

It's easy enough for me to mark it with a tag under the covers, _however_, it would be really nice to just set it in the cell's metadata (or even using the `metadata.name` attribute):

```json
{
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "papermill": {
          "parameter_cell": true
        }
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "x = 3\n",
        "y=3"
      ]
    },
  ],
  "metadata": {},
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 2
}
```

What do you all think? Would `papermill` be open to looking for this metadata in addition to the current tagging mechanism?

